<html>

<head>
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.1.3/css/bootstrap.min.css">
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="/main.css"/>
</head>

<body>
  <div class="container">

  <div class="pb-2 mt-4 mb-2">
    <h1>Say My Name</h1>
  </div>

  <div>
    <p>Now here we are on this other page, doing something. I have no idea what your name is, internet stranger. You just asked for this page, you got it.</p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h4>Request body say your name is: <%= nameFromBody %></h4>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h4>Cookie say your name is: <%= locals.nameFromCookie %></h4>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h4>Session say your name is: <%= locals.nameFromSession %></h4>
  </div>

  <div>
    <p>If you look at your Network panel, you can see the Request Headers for this page included a 'Cookie' header with <code>nameCookie</code> and <code>connect.sid</code>. (<em>Request</em> because the cookies are going from client to server).</p>

    <p>Importantly, if you open a new tab and type in:</p>
    <pre>http://localhost:8080/nameContinue</pre>
    <p>the cookie and session will still be there.</p>

    <p>Cookies have an <code>maxAge</code> setting that <em>asks</em> the browser to keep them (and keep sending them) that long. If it is not specified, the cookie is deleted when you close your browser.</p>
  </div>


  <div>
    <p><a href="name">(Go back)</a></p>
  </div>

  </div>
</body>

</html>